---json
{
  "layout": "layouts/t-hub.njk",
  "permalink": "/accounting/services/",
  "slug": "acct-svc-hub",
  "tierClass": "section--tier-hub",
  "bodyClass": "page--hub",
  "title": "Accounting Services Catalog · TechBrot",
  "description": "Our full accounting services catalog — monthly bookkeeping, QuickBooks setup, cleanup, migration, payroll, sales tax, and fractional CFO. Fixed-fee.",
  "breadcrumb": [
    { "name": "Home", "href": "/" },
    { "name": "Accounting", "href": "/accounting/" },
    { "name": "Services" }
  ],
  "hero": {
    "eyebrow": "Service catalog",
    "heading": "Accounting services, scoped properly. Priced honestly.",
    "subheading": "Seven core service tracks &mdash; monthly bookkeeping, QuickBooks setup and cleanup, migration, payroll management, sales tax compliance, and fractional CFO. Every engagement is fixed-fee with a written scope before any work begins, delivered by Certified Intuit ProAdvisors. Independent firm.",
    "actions": [
      { "label": "Book the discovery call", "href": "/contact/?intent=accounting", "class": "btn--primary" },
      { "label": "Get the free file review", "href": "/quickbooks/file-review/?intent=file-review", "class": "btn--ghost" }
    ]
  },
  "summary": "<strong>The TechBrot service catalog:</strong> monthly &middot; cleanup &middot; catch-up bookkeeping &middot; QuickBooks (setup, cleanup, migration) &middot; payroll management &middot; multi-state sales tax compliance &middot; fractional CFO &mdash; seven engagement types, each fixed-fee with a written scope before any work begins, delivered by Certified Intuit ProAdvisors across all 50 states.",
  "summarySource": "Independent Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor firm &mdash; we keep the books; your CPA files. Not affiliated with Intuit Inc.",
  "ctaBand": {
    "eyebrow": "Start here",
    "heading": "Scope your engagement.",
    "lede": "A free 30-minute discovery call, then a written fixed-fee scope within 3 business days &mdash; the right engagement and the exact fee, in writing, before you commit. If we&rsquo;re not the right fit, we&rsquo;ll say so.",
    "actions": [
      { "label": "Book the discovery call", "href": "/contact/?intent=accounting", "class": "btn--primary" },
      { "label": "Speak to a ProAdvisor", "tel": true, "class": "btn--ghost" }
    ]
  },
  "sec": {
    "summaryId": "acct-svc-hub-in-brief-text",
    "summaryTag": "In one paragraph",
    "summaryH": "The TechBrot service catalog, summarized.",
    "aiH": "The service catalog, in five questions.",
    "faqTag": "Services FAQ",
    "faqH": "Questions about the catalog."
  }
}
---

{# ── TRACKS — seven engagement types (dc-card hub-card r-3, white). (H2: Seven engagement types. Distinct work, distinct outcomes.) ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="acct-svc-hub-tracks">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">The service tracks</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:30ch;margin-bottom:10px;">Seven engagement types. Distinct work, distinct outcomes.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 32px;max-width:64ch;">Each track links to full scope, deliverables, cadence, and pricing detail. Or use the diagnostic below if you&rsquo;re not sure which engagement fits your situation.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for s in tracks %}
      <article class="dc-card hub-card"><span class="eyebrow">{{ s.eyebrow | safe }}</span><h3>{{ s.name | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:15px;margin:6px 0 12px;">{{ s.body | safe }}</p><p class="mono" style="font-size:12px;color:var(--color-ink-mute);margin:0 0 8px;"><strong style="color:var(--color-ink);">{{ s.fee | safe }}</strong> &middot; {{ s.eng | safe }}</p><p class="prose" style="font-size:13px;margin:0 0 12px;color:var(--color-ink-mute);"><strong style="color:var(--color-ink);">Best for:</strong> {{ s.best | safe }}</p><a class="hub-card__go" href="{{ s.href }}">{{ s.name | safe }} <svg width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 12h15M13 6l6 6-6 6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></a></article>
      {%- endfor %}
      <article class="dc-card hub-card"><span class="eyebrow">{{ cfo.eyebrow | safe }}</span><h3>{{ cfo.name | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:15px;margin:6px 0 12px;">{{ cfo.lede | safe }}</p><p class="mono" style="font-size:12px;color:var(--color-ink-mute);margin:0 0 8px;"><strong style="color:var(--color-ink);">{{ cfo.fee | safe }}</strong> &middot; {{ cfo.eng | safe }}</p><p class="prose" style="font-size:13px;margin:0 0 12px;color:var(--color-ink-mute);"><strong style="color:var(--color-ink);">Best for:</strong> {{ cfo.best | safe }}</p><a class="hub-card__go" href="{{ cfo.href }}">{{ cfo.name | safe }} <svg width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 12h15M13 6l6 6-6 6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></a></article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── DIAGNOSTIC — six situations (dc-card r-3, sand). (H2: Which engagement do you actually need?) ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="acct-svc-hub-diagnostic" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Find your situation</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:24ch;margin-bottom:10px;">Which engagement do you actually need?</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 32px;max-width:64ch;">Most buyers don&rsquo;t know exactly which service fits &mdash; they know something&rsquo;s wrong. Below are the six most common situations and the engagement that fits each.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for d in diagnostic %}
      <div class="dc-card"><h3>{{ d.q | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:15px;margin:8px 0 0;"><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> {{ d.diagnosis | safe }}</p><p class="prose" style="font-size:15px;margin:8px 0 0;"><strong>Right path:</strong> {{ d.path | safe }}</p><p class="prose" style="font-size:15px;margin:8px 0 0;"><strong>Typical fee:</strong> {{ d.fee | safe }}</p><a class="hub-card__go" href="{{ d.href }}">{{ d.cta | safe }} <svg width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 12h15M13 6l6 6-6 6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></a></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── PRICING — all engagements in one view (vs-table, white). (H2: All engagement pricing in one view.) ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="acct-svc-hub-pricing">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Pricing at a glance</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:26ch;margin-bottom:10px;">All engagement pricing in one view.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 30px;max-width:64ch;">Every TechBrot engagement is fixed-fee with a written scope before any work begins. No hourly billing. Specific quotes follow the free discovery call.</p>
    <table class="cmp">
      <caption class="sr-only">TechBrot accounting service pricing summary across all engagement tracks.</caption>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th scope="col">Service track</th>
          <th scope="col">Engagement type</th>
          <th scope="col" class="num us">Fee range</th>
          <th scope="col">Cadence</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {%- for row in pricing %}
        <tr>
          <th scope="row" data-col="Service track"><a href="{{ row.href }}">{{ row.service | safe }}</a></th>
          <td data-col="Engagement type">{{ row.type | safe }}</td>
          <td class="num us" data-col="Fee range"><strong>{{ row.fee | safe }}</strong></td>
          <td data-col="Cadence">{{ row.cadence | safe }}</td>
        </tr>
        {%- endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p class="in-brief__source">All engagements: fixed fee, written scope before any work begins, no hourly billing. Specific quotes are produced within 3 business days of the free, no-obligation discovery call.</p>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── DELIVERY MODES — direct vs vetted-local (incl-card r-2, sand). (H2: Direct service or curated network.) ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="acct-svc-hub-delivery" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">How we deliver</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:24ch;margin-bottom:10px;">Direct service or curated network.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:64ch;">Two delivery modes, one operating standard. Engagements route based on what the work requires &mdash; your location, industry, and the specific service needed.</p>
    <div class="r-2">
      {%- for m in modes %}
      <article class="incl-card">
        <span class="eyebrow">{{ m.eyebrow | safe }}</span>
        <h3>{{ m.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose" style="font-size:15px;margin:8px 0 0;">{{ m.lede | safe }}</p>
        <ul class="checklist">
          {%- for p in m.points %}
          <li>{{ p | safe }}</li>
          {%- endfor %}
        </ul>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── STANDARDS — six engagement standards (process-grid, white). (H2: What every TechBrot engagement includes.) ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="acct-svc-hub-standards">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Engagement standards</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:26ch;margin-bottom:10px;">What every TechBrot engagement includes.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 30px;max-width:64ch;">Regardless of service track, every engagement runs to the same operating standards. The standards are the platform; the services are the application of them.</p>
    <div class="process-grid">
      {%- for s in standards %}
      <div class="process-step">
        <span class="process-step__n">0{{ loop.index }}</span>
        <h3>{{ s.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p>{{ s.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── CATALOG REVIEW & STANDARDS — prose + trust-row (sand, read). (H2: Service catalog maintained by the TechBrot platform team.) ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="acct-svc-hub-review" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct read">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Catalog standards</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:18px;">Service catalog maintained by the TechBrot platform team.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>This catalog is maintained by the platform team at TechBrot Inc., a Delaware-incorporated independent Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor firm. Pricing ranges, engagement structures, and service descriptions reflect current operational practice. Pricing is reviewed quarterly; service-track definitions update as the firm&rsquo;s capabilities expand. For a current quote on any specific engagement, the 30-minute discovery call is the right path &mdash; specific quotes are delivered within three business days of the call.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for r in reviewSpec %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ r.value | safe }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ r.label | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="in-brief__source">Catalog last reviewed: May 2026.</p>
  </div>
</section>
